article.description: Conner Toolson scored a career-high 29 points and Utah Valley held on to beat Texas-San Antonio 75-71 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Toolson scores 29 points; Utah Valley beats UTSA 75-71
article.linkText: Toolson scores 29 points; Utah Valley beats UTSA 75-71
article.story: OREM, Utah -- Conner Toolson scored a career-high 29 points and Utah Valley held on to beat Texas-San Antonio 75-71 on Saturday night. Toolson was 12 of 18 from the field and made three 3-pointers. Kenneth Ogbe had 12 points and Hayden Schenck added 10 for Utah Valley (5-2). Brandon Randolph had eight assists and Isaac Neilson grabbed 11 rebounds. Nick Billingsley scored 21 points on 8-of-17 shooting to lead UTSA (2-6). Nick Allen added 17 points. The game was tied 58-58 with 4:44 to play. Ogbe made a 3-pointer, sparking an 11-4 spurt to give the Wolverines a 69-62 lead with about two minutes left. Schenck made a layup and a pair of free throws during the stretch. Billingsley made a 3-pointer to pull the Roadrunners to 71-68 with 28 seconds left but they didn't get closer.
